HSC Survey Results

German Bank Survey # 6 Results from 11/10/2023

Survey Details

5 commercial purse seiners conducted this fishing survey on 11/10/2023 starting at 20:00:00.

All vessels ran two transects in the German Bank box and one transect in the Seal Island Box.

There was a plankton tow and replicate conducted and CTD cast by Lady Janice II.

A total of 250 tags were applied during the survey over 1 event(s) from 2023-10-12 to 2023-10-12 from 1 vessel(s).

Samples were obtained for target strength estimation.

Acoustic Equipment

Each vessel was equipped with a Simrad ES38-18/200-18C combi (2-in-1) transducer prior to the survey that contains a 38kHz split beam and 200 kHz single beam transducer. Data was logged to the computer hard-drive for post-processing. All participating boats were calibrated on 38kHz before the survey.

Survey Results

Main Results

The results are subject to change as DFO will re-evaluate data editing, area estimation and apply a target strength.

Preliminary biomass prediction for German Bank using standardized parallel transects is 23,614mt, and with turnover applied 20,057mt. The preliminary biomass estimate for Seal Island is 15,261mt.

Vessel Performance

Speed

Average vessel speed was 8.59. This is above the 8 knot requirement; vessels are urged to slow down to prevent backscatter noise from interfering with the acoustic data.

Distance

No significant distance was cut from the planned lines; vessels covered the planned area well.
